ing child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a success. Do not mix implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260513T012638-681e6f3c/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260513T012638-681e6f3c/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;To request orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260513T012638-681e6f3c/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260513T012638-681e6f3c/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Decomposition depth cap\u0026#xA;This bead is already at decomposition depth 3. Do not create another child layer; if it is still too large, reject the split with a short explanation and write no_changes_rationale.txt instead.\u0026#xA;\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-7c256284\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eImplement Story 16 run resolver bodies, tool calls, and bundle confinement\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;The run-detail page needs a single GraphQL/data-layer contract that can return transcript bodies, normalized tool calls, and evidence bundle file metadata without exposing arbitrary filesystem paths.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/server/graphql/schema.graphql:1208-1216 defines the run-detail transcript and bundleFiles fields on Run.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/server/graphql/schema.graphql:1232-1266 defines RunToolCall and RunToolCallConnection, and cli/internal/server/graphql/schema.graphql:2794-2822 defines run(id:), runToolCalls, and runBundleFile.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/server/state_runs_detail.go:16-30 defines the 64 KB cap and inline whitelist; cli/internal/server/state_runs_detail.go:102-140 is the bundle path confinement boundary.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/server/state_runs_detail.go:247-290 loads prompt, response, stderr, and bundleFiles; cli/internal/server/state_runs_detail.go:308-384 resolves persisted tool calls and bundle files.\u0026#xA;- Parent context: ddx-b4c5151a, originally split from ddx-70a432b5. Preserve dependency IDs ddx-f04faa86 and ddx-4cd64068 when filing this child.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;Ensure run(id:) returns prompt, response, stderr, and bundleFiles[] for try/run records; ensure runToolCalls(id:, first:, after:) pages drain-time normalized ToolCallEntry records; ensure runBundleFile(id:, path:) rejects absolute paths, traversal, and symlink escapes, returns nil for missing/forbidden files, and inlines only whitelisted files under 64 KB.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Frontend implementation; Story 16.1 and Story 16.2 own the production page and evidence tab.\u0026#xA;- New auth or role-based access control beyond existing project-scoped run visibility.\u0026#xA;- Spec prose updates, raw-transcript audit event semantics, and Playwright e2e coverage assigned to sibling child beads.\u0026#xA;- Do not implement parent acceptance criteria assigned to sibling child beads.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. TestRunToolCalls_PersistedAtDrain and TestSessionIndexEntryFromResult_PersistsToolCalls pass and prove tool calls come from persisted ToolCallEntry data rather than log reparsing.\u0026#xA;2. TestRunBundleFile_PathTraversalRejected, TestRunBundleFile_SymlinkEscapeRejected, TestRunBundleFile_SizeCap, TestRunBundleFile_WhitelistEnforcement, TestRunBundleFile_MissingPathReturns404, and TestRunBundleFiles_Listing pass.\u0026#xA;3. TestIntegration_Query_Runs passes with run(id:) returning layer details and transcript-capable fields without GraphQL errors.\u0026#xA;4. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/server/... -run \u0026#39;TestRunToolCalls_PersistedAtDrain|TestSessionIndexEntryFromResult_PersistsToolCalls|TestRunBundleFile_|TestRunBundleFiles_Listing|TestIntegration_Query_Runs\u0026#39; passes.\u0026#xA;5. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./... passes.\u0026#xA;6. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, story:16, area:server, area:graphql, kind:feature, spec:FEAT-010, decomposed, needs-human-decomposition\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-f129bfaf\" base-rev=\"cdcf4585f85351b143f7080982acce9313592f66\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260513T012638-681e6f3c\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260513T012638-681e6f3c","base_rev":"cdcf4585f85351b143f7080982ac